data.description: Welcome home! This expansive seven bedroom colonial features plenty of stately charm and a 3-story canvas for you to breathe new life into. The former home of famed restauranteur and co-owner of London Chop House, Sam Gruber, is situated in Detroit's prestigious Palmer Woods subdivision on a sprawling half acre of land. Rich with all of the historic details one might expect of a home from this period, hand plastered crown molding, custom Spanish-style tile work, arched ceilings, custom built-ins and plastered medallions. Each room offers its own unique story with several elements of the home, including the sunroom, having been featured in the local newspaper for the design prowess. Four of the seven bedrooms offer an en suite bathroom and the primary suite boasts a walk-in closet. The third floor offers two additional bedrooms and a full bathroom. Located a short walk from dining and shopping on the Livernois Avenue of Fashion. Schedule your showing and submit your offer today!
